      "description": "Raatikainen's snare on *Follow the Reaper* was a Tama Starclassic maple model, matched to the kit's shell series and suited to the extraordinary technical demands of the album's arrangements. The 14\" x 5.5\" dimensions delivered the crack and attack essential for blast beat sections and the rapid single-stroke work that defines tracks like \"Kissing the Shadows,\" with enough body and warmth to remain musical alongside Janne Wirman's dense keyboard layers.\n\nThe Starclassic maple snare's construction gave it a warmer, more complex character than steel or brass alternatives — a deliberate choice for an album where the drums needed to serve neoclassical compositions rather than compete with them. Children of Bodom's arrangements placed heavy musical value on the interplay between guitar, keyboard, and drums, and a hyper-aggressive metal snare would have disrupted that balance in Anssi Kippo's mix.\n\nThe result is a snare sound on *Follow the Reaper* that is aggressive, precise, and present without overwhelming the melodic content — the correct tool for arguably CoB's most technically demanding studio performance.",
