      "description": "For *Are You Dead Yet?*, Jaska Raatikainen transitioned to the Pearl Masters Premium Maple — Pearl's professional-grade production shell line and the beginning of an endorsement relationship that would carry through the remainder of Children of Bodom's career. The shift from Tama Starclassic Maple brought a different construction philosophy and a noticeably different tonal character to CoB's drum sound.\n\nPearl's Masters Premium Maple shells are built around a six-ply all-maple construction with tighter manufacturing tolerances than the Tama Starclassic's approach. The result is a more focused, immediate attack with less sustain resonance — a sound well-suited to the more mid-paced, groove-oriented arrangements that *Are You Dead Yet?* favoured compared to the sustained-velocity extremity of *Follow the Reaper* and *Hate Crew Deathroll*.\n\nThe double bass drum configuration — twin 22\" x 18\" kick drums — remained central to Raatikainen's setup, now paired with the Pearl Eliminator double pedal. Even with *Are You Dead Yet?*'s shift toward more accessible tempos, Children of Bodom's arrangements still required the double-kick foundation as a structural element: tracks like \"In Your Face\" and \"Are You Dead Yet?\" deploy double-bass patterns not as continuous velocity showcases but as dynamic punctuation within groove-centred arrangements.\n\nThe compact tom spread — 10\" and 12\" rack toms, 14\" and 16\" floor toms — continued from the Tama era, maintaining the tonal range for CoB's melodic fill language in a new shell construction context. The Pearl Masters' more focused attack meant that the melody-following fill work registered with a different character than the warmer, more open Starclassic sound.",
