      "description": "Raatikainen's snare on *Are You Dead Yet?* was a Pearl Masters maple model — matched to the kit's shell series and consistent with the overall Pearl endorsement transition. The 14\" x 5.5\" dimensions maintained the dimensions of his Tama Starclassic snare while the Pearl construction brought a subtly different character: tighter maple construction producing a slightly more focused crack with less shell resonance than the Starclassic model.\n\nThe Pearl Masters snare's character suited the more groove-oriented arrangements on *Are You Dead Yet?* well. Where the *Hate Crew Deathroll* snare sound — recorded at Finnvox Studios with Mikko Karmila's production — emphasized the aggressive leading edge, Anssi Kippo's Astia Studio approach with the Pearl snare produced a sound that balanced attack with body, fitting the album's more mid-paced, accessible arrangements.\n\nGhost notes and dynamic snare work are more prominent on *Are You Dead Yet?* than on any previous CoB album — reflecting both the more groove-centred song structures and the Pearl snare's natural dynamics across a wider dynamic range than blast-and-fill-dominated playing requires.",
