        "answer": "On *Are You Dead Yet?* (2005), Jaska Raatikainen transitioned to Pearl Masters Premium Maple drums — his first Pearl album, marking the beginning of an endorsement relationship that would continue through Children of Bodom's career. The setup centered on twin 22\" x 18\" bass drums, rack toms (10\" and 12\"), and floor toms (14\" and 16\"), all in Pearl's six-ply maple construction. This was the beginning of the Pearl Masters era that replaced the Tama Starclassic Maple of *Hate Crew Deathroll* (2003). For Raatikainen's complete gear history, see the [Jaska Raatikainen drummer profile](/drummer/jaska-raatikainen)."
