        "answer": "Jaska Raatikainen used the Pearl Eliminator double pedal on *Are You Dead Yet?* (2005) — his transition from the Tama Iron Cobra of the Starclassic era. The Eliminator's interchangeable cam system allowed him to dial in a specific response feel suited to *Are You Dead Yet?*'s more groove-oriented arrangements: controlled beater follow-through for mid-paced patterns, with the capability for full double-kick velocity when tracks like \"In Your Face\" demanded it. The Pearl Eliminator would remain his pedal choice through the remainder of CoB's career. See the [Jaska Raatikainen full kit guide](/articles/jaska-raatikainen-drum-setup) for his complete pedal history."
