      "description": "For *Relentless Reckless Forever*, Jaska Raatikainen played the Pearl Masters MCX — the evolved Pearl Masters shell construction that refined the six-ply maple configuration of the earlier Premium Maple era into a more precisely voiced instrument. Captured at Sonic Pump Studios with the accumulated studio knowledge of three CoB albums in that environment, the MCX kit produced the most focused and consistent Pearl-era drum sound in CoB's catalog.\n\nThe Pearl Masters MCX shell construction brought improved resonance characteristics compared to the earlier Premium Maple: enhanced shell stiffness and more uniform maple ply selection produced a more immediate attack transient and a tighter, more controlled sustain. In Sonic Pump Studios' acoustic environment — which Anssi Kippo had learned thoroughly across *Blooddrunk* — the MCX shells' attack-forward character translated directly to the mix with minimal post-processing.\n\nThe double bass drum configuration — twin 22\" x 18\" kick drums — remained the cornerstone of Raatikainen's approach, deployed across *Relentless Reckless Forever*'s varied tempo landscape. \"Shovel Knockout\" drives sustained double-kick patterns through the verse-to-chorus architecture; the slower, more melodic tracks allowed the MCX shells' controlled sustain to serve the arrangements without the kick-focused high-velocity context.\n\nThe compact tom spread — 10\" and 12\" rack toms, 14\" and 16\" floor toms — maintained the CoB fill vocabulary: Janne Wirman's keyboard lines tracked by melodic tom phrases that serve as compositional countermelody rather than pure rhythmic punctuation. In the MCX's more precisely voiced character, these fill passages had a clarity and definition that suited *Relentless Reckless Forever*'s refined production.",
