      "description": "Raatikainen's snare on *Relentless Reckless Forever* was a Pearl Masters MCX model — the evolved shell construction that brought the same refined character to the snare as to the kit's tom and bass drum shells. The 14\" x 5.5\" dimensions delivered focused crack and attack suited to the album's varied tempo demands, with the MCX construction's tighter sustain providing cleaner articulation in Anssi Kippo's dense keyboard-layered mix.\n\nThe album's dynamic range — from the sustained aggression of \"Shovel Knockout\" to the more measured architectural approach of slower tracks — required the snare to serve multiple roles: high-impact backbeat work at full velocity, ghost note passages in verse arrangements, and precise accent placement across fill phrases. The MCX snare's focused attack served all these roles with the confidence of a deeply familiar instrument.\n\nKippo's Sonic Pump Studios treatment of the MCX snare reflected six years of accumulated knowledge with Pearl Masters shells in this environment: close-miked signal treated to preserve the natural MCX attack character, with compression and EQ dialed to Raatikainen's playing dynamics and the album's production priorities.",
