      "description": "Jaska Raatikainen's Zildjian A Custom and K Custom cymbal setup on *Relentless Reckless Forever* was the settled, fully understood configuration of the Pearl endorsement peak — the same arrangement that had debuted on *Are You Dead Yet?* (2005) and been refined through *Blooddrunk* (2008), now deployed with six years of accumulated familiarity.\n\nThe Zildjian A Custom series' multi-stage lathing and brilliant finish remained the right choice for CoB's keyboard-dense production approach: the A Custom's bright, cutting character allowed cymbal work to register clearly in Janne Wirman's synth-heavy arrangements without requiring significant EQ assistance in the mix. The fast attack and bright upper frequency presence of the A Custom 14\" hi-hats maintained articulation clarity across *Relentless Reckless Forever*'s varied tempo demands.\n\nBy *Relentless Reckless Forever*, the A Custom / K Custom combination had been in Raatikainen's hands for six years of touring and recording. The familiarity is audible in the placement precision: crashes land at structurally significant moments with the deliberateness of a drummer who knows exactly what each cymbal sounds like in every dynamic context, rather than a player still learning the instrument's character.\n\nThe K Custom 20\" ride's darker bell and body character continued to serve its role as textural counterpoint to the brighter A Custom crashes — warmth for sustained melodic passages and keyboard-driven sections, bright cut from the A Custom for high-velocity transitions and intensity peaks. The China cymbal deployment on *Relentless Reckless Forever* maintained the prominent role established on *Blooddrunk*, serving the structural articulation moments of \"Shovel Knockout\" and similar tracks.",
