        "answer": "On *Relentless Reckless Forever* (2011), Jaska Raatikainen used Pearl Masters MCX drums — an evolved Pearl Masters shell construction from the Premium Maple configuration of earlier albums, brought to its most refined expression on this seventh CoB studio record. The setup centered on twin 22\" x 18\" bass drums, rack toms (10\" and 12\"), and floor toms (14\" and 16\") in the MCX's improved maple construction. For Raatikainen's complete gear history across Children of Bodom's career, see the [Jaska Raatikainen drummer profile](/drummer/jaska-raatikainen)."
